25|$|The 1991 {{uprising}} in Sulaymaniyah {{was one of}} the biggest 1991 uprisings in Iraq. Sulaymaniyah, <b>a</b> <b>Kurdish</b> city of over 100,000 population, was the first Iraqi city to be captured by rebels and the last one to fall. The city was recaptured by Kurdish rebels, after the Peshmerga launched a new offensive on 20 July.|$|E
